column5: Friends are heading up next week. Any reports on crappie and walleye success in the Obabikon/Hay Island area? Thanks
Been catching crappies in Obabikon for the last few weeks. Nothing yet At Hay Island.
Richard, Thanks for the info. I really enjoy your periodic journal on your web site. What's the surface temperature running now? Thanks

Bill, I hope this is not too late. Returned from LOTW (Morson) yesterday. Spent Monday afternoon (9/13) in Obabikon fishing crappies - caught our limit in 2-3 hours - mostly in the "elbow" area. Tom502
Any more updates for LOW would be great. I am leaving Friday for the Nestor Falls area and would appreciate any information. Thanks
Tom, Thanks for the reply. One group left today, another this weekend.
Bubbalou I here there are two bites going on is shallow and the other one is deep. Wish I didn't have to work this year otherwise would be up there.
